What is the functionality of the following code?
```java
public void function (Node node) {
  if(size == 0)
    head = node;
  else{
    Node temp, cur;
    for(cur = head;
        (temp = cur.getNext())! = null; cur = temp);
    cur.setNext(node);
  }
  size++;
}
```
(i) Inserting a node at the beginning of the list
(ii) Deleting a node at the beginning of the list
(iii) Inserting a node at the end of the list
(iv) Deleting a node at the end of the list

Which of the following is time complexity of the given code?
```cpp
int a = 0;
for (i = 0; i<N; i++) {
  for (j = N; j>i; j--){
    a = a + i + j;
  }
}
```
(i) O(N)
(ii) O(N*log(N))
(iii) O(N*Sqrt(N))
(iv) O(N*N)

Which of the following is time complexity of the given code?
```cpp
int i, j, k = 0;
for (i = n/2; i<= n; i++) {
  for (j = 2; j<= n; j = j*2) {
    k = k + n/2;
  }
}
```
(i) O(N)
(ii) O(N*log(N))
(iii) O(N*Sqrt(N))
(iv) O(N*N)

Analyse the time complexity of the given function and also write the recurrence relation of the function :
```cpp
int DoSomething (int n)
{
  if (n<= 2)
    return 1;
  else
    return (DoSomething (floor(sqrt(n)))+n);
}
```

What is the time complexity of the following code snippet?
```cpp
for(i=0; i<n; i++){
  for(j=0; j<i; j++){
    int sum= i + j;
  }
}
```
(i) O(n)
(ii) O(n^2)
(iii) O(log n)
(iv) O(1)

