Which class/set of classes can illustrate polymorphism in the following code
```cpp
abstract class student? {
public: int marks;
  calc_grade();
};
class topper: public student {
public: calc_grade() { return 10; }
};
class average: public student {
public: calc_grade() { return 20; }
};
class failed{int marks;};
```
(i) Only class student can show polymorphism
(ii) Only class student and topper together can show polymorphism
(iii) All class students, topper and average together can show polymorphism
(iv) Class failed should also inherit class student for this code to work for polymorphism

